A vintage 1960s technical illustration showing a retro filing cabinet with multiple brass connectors and cables emerging from its drawers, each cable ending in different geometric shapes that plug into a central modernist hub device. The scene is rendered in muted olive greens, burnt orange, and cream colors with halftone dot patterns and aged paper texture. Brass knobs and mechanical switches adorn the equipment. The composition suggests seamless connection and organization, with a warm nostalgic quality reminiscent of mid-century corporate technical manuals.
